/// WedLM-DS: WedLM-7B with DeepSeek-V3 Architectural Innovations
///
/// Full model design for the WedLM-DeepSeek hybrid architecture.
/// Combines WedLM-7B (text-diffusion on Qwen2.5-7B backbone) with:
/// - Multi-Head Latent Attention (MLA) — 93% KV cache reduction
/// - Learnable residual weights — improved training stability
/// - SwiGLU feed-forward networks
///
/// Architecture:
///   Token IDs -> Embedding -> 28 x WedLMDSBlock -> DenoisingHead -> Token Logits
///
/// Hyperparameters (Qwen2.5-7B compatible):
///   dim = 3584, num_heads = 28, layers = 28
///   kv_lora_rank = 512, q_lora_rank = 1536, v_head_dim = 128
///   d_ff = 18944, vocab_size = 152064
///
/// Training objective: Masked diffusion (MDLM-style)
///   - Tokens randomly masked during forward pass
///   - DenoisingHead predicts original tokens
///   - Loss: cross-entropy on masked positions
///
/// Reference: WedLM-DeepSeek Hybrid Architecture design doc
neuron WedLMDS(vocab_size=152064, dim=3584, num_heads=28, kv_lora_rank=512, q_lora_rank=1536, v_head_dim=128, d_ff=18944, layers=28):
    in: [batch, seq]
    out: [batch, seq, vocab_size]
    context:
        stack = unroll(layers):
            block = WedLMDSBlock(dim, num_heads, kv_lora_rank, q_lora_rank, v_head_dim, d_ff)
    graph:
        # Embed token IDs into hidden states
        in -> Embedding(vocab_size, dim) -> embedded

        # Stack of transformer blocks
        embedded ->
            stack
            hidden

        # Denoising prediction head
        hidden -> DenoisingHead(dim, vocab_size) -> out
